---
source: crates/shannon-tools/tests/tool_schema_snapshots.rs
assertion_line: 60
expression: output
---
Agent: Spawn and manage AI agent teammates for collaborative problem-solving
AnalyzeImage: Analyze an image file or URL. The image is sent to the LLM for visual analysis based on your prompt. Supports PNG, JPEG, GIF, WebP, BMP, ICO, and TIFF formats.
Bash: Executes bash commands and returns output
Brief: Generate a concise task summary from conversation history or content
Config: Manage runtime configuration with get, set, list, delete, and reset operations
Cron: Schedule recurring or one-shot prompts for time-based task execution
DocsQuery: Fetch up-to-date documentation for libraries and frameworks. Resolves package names via docs.rs (Rust), npm (JavaScript/TypeScript), and PyPI (Python). Returns documentation snippets useful for writing correct code.
Edit: Perform exact string replacements in files
GitBranch: List, create, switch, and delete git branches
GitDiff: Show git diffs with support for staged, unstaged, and commit range diffs
GitLog: View git commit history with filtering and formatting options
GitSafety: Check if a git command is safe before executing it
GitStash: Manage git stashes: list, push, pop, drop, and apply stashed changes
Glob: Fast file pattern matching tool that works with any codebase size
Grep: A powerful search tool built on ripgrep. Searches file contents using regex patterns. Supports include/exclude globs, context lines, case-insensitive matching, and multiple output modes.
McpAuth: Manage OAuth authentication for MCP servers that require it
McpResource: Read and list resources from MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers
MergeResolve: Resolve merge conflict markers in a file by choosing 'ours' or 'theirs' for each conflict
MultiEdit: Apply multiple file edits atomically — all edits succeed or none are applied
NotebookEdit: Edit Jupyter notebook (.ipynb) cells - replace, insert, or delete cells
PowerShell: Executes PowerShell commands and returns output
REPL: Execute a REPL command that wraps primitive tool calls for batch operations
Read: Read file contents from the local filesystem
ScheduleWakeup: Schedule a prompt to be enqueued after a delay (for /loop dynamic pacing). Call with delaySeconds and prompt to schedule; omit or call without arguments to end the loop. Cache optimization: delays <= 270s keep the prompt cache warm; 270-300s risks cache expiry; > 300s pays cold read cost. Prefer 270s for active work, 600s+ for idle waits.
SendMessage: Send messages to agent teammates for collaborative problem-solving
Skill: Invoke user-callable slash-command skills for specialized workflows
Sleep: Wait for a specified duration without holding a shell process
StructuredOutput: Return structured output in the requested format. Call this tool exactly once at the end of your response to provide the structured output.
Task: Create and manage tasks for tracking work progress
TaskCreate: Create a new task with subject, description, and optional metadata
TaskGet: Get details of a specific task by ID
TaskList: List all tasks with optional status filter
TaskOutput: Get the output/result of a task execution by its ID
TaskStop: Stop or cancel a running task by its ID
TaskUpdate: Update an existing task's status, subject, or description
TeamDelete: Remove a team and clean up its associated task list
TodoWrite: Create and manage session task checklists for tracking work progress
WebFetch: Fetches a URL from the internet and optionally extracts its contents
WebSearch: Search the web for information using a real search API
Worktree: Manage git worktree sessions for isolated branch work
Write: Write content to a file, overwriting if it exists
ask_user_question: Ask the user a question during execution. Supports single-select, multi-select, and free-text input. Use this when you need confirmation, option selection, or information from the user.
auto_commit: Smart git commit tool. Stages changes (all or specific files), generates semantic commit messages from diffs, and creates commits. Supports dry-run preview and co-author trailers. Shows git status and diff stats before committing.
code_actions: Get available code actions (quick fixes, refactorings) for a range in a file. Uses the language server to suggest fixes for diagnostics and available refactorings.
computer: Interact with the computer desktop: take screenshots, click, type, scroll, and press keys. Coordinates are in [0-1024, 0-768] range and scaled to actual screen resolution.
document_symbol: List all symbols (functions, classes, methods, variables, etc.) in a file. Uses the language server to provide a hierarchical view of the document's symbol structure.
enter_plan_mode: Enter plan mode for read-only analysis and planning. File modifications will be disabled.
exit_plan_mode: Exit plan mode and return to normal editing mode.
find_references: Find all references to the symbol at a given position in a file. Uses the language server to locate all usages of a symbol across the codebase.
get_mcp_prompt: Get a prompt from an MCP (Model Context Protocol) server. Provide server_name, prompt_name, and optional arguments to retrieve the prompt messages.
get_plan_status: Get the current plan mode status, including active state and any plan content.
gh_issue_list: List GitHub issues for the current repository
gh_issue_view: View a specific GitHub issue with comments
gh_pr_create: Create a pull request on GitHub
gh_pr_list: List pull requests for the current repository
gh_pr_view: View a specific pull request with optional diff
go_to_definition: Find the definition of the symbol at a given position in a file. Uses the language server (e.g., rust-analyzer) to locate where a symbol is defined.
hover: Get type information and documentation for the symbol at a given position. Uses the language server to provide hover information such as type signatures, doc comments, and other contextual information.
list_mcp_prompts: List available prompts from MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers. Returns prompt names, descriptions, and argument schemas. Optionally filter by server_name.
list_mcp_resources: List available resources from MCP (Model Context Protocol) servers. Returns resource URIs, names, descriptions, and MIME types. Optionally filter by server_name.
read_mcp_resource: Read the content of a specific MCP (Model Context Protocol) resource by providing the server name and resource URI. Returns the resource content as text.
rename_symbol: Rename a symbol (variable, function, class, etc.) across the entire codebase. Uses the language server to find all occurrences and compute the correct edits for renaming.
workspace_symbol: Search for symbols across the entire workspace by name. Uses the language server to find functions, classes, structs, etc. matching a query pattern across all files in the project.
